oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Millet for pasture
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A portion of dairy herd grazing on Starr Millet seeded about the middle of August 1960. Seeded on Dickson soil. Treatment four hundred pounds of 6-12-12 and seventy-five pounds ammonia nitrate per acre. Fourteen cows have grazed about two weeks on this six-acre millet.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
